  "text": "One who tears two stitches to sew, in order to sew two stitches, is liable. But one who tears to ruin it, is exempt, since he is destroying. One who tears in his anger or for a dead person for whom he is obligated to tear [in mourning] is liable, because his mind is put at ease with this thing and his impulse is calmed. And since his anger is assuaged with this thing, it is like he is improving [something], so he is liable. And one who [tears to] open a collar on Shabbat is liable.",
